Date: Thu 25 Mar 2010
Source: The Poultry site [edited]
<http://www.thepoultrysite.com/poultrynews/19805/five-new-bird-flu-outbreaks-in-viet-nam>


New Bird Flu Outbreaks in Viet Nam
----------------------------------
A total of 5 new outbreaks of highly pathogenic avian influenza (HPAI)
have been reported. The veterinary authority has sent Follow Up Report
No. 41 dated 24 Mar 2010 to the World Organisation for Animal Health
(OIE).

The report covers 5 outbreaks starting between 28 Feb and 15 Mar 2010.
They occurred in the north and in the south of the country; 3 were on
farms and 2 were in village flocks. In total, 5208 were involved, of
which 2442 died and 2766 were destroyed.

The presence of the H5N1 sub-type of the virus has been confirmed.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Mary Marshall

[The HPAI H5N1 epizootic in Viet Nam has been continuing since
December 2006. On 24 Mar 2010, the 41st follow-up report was sent to
the OIE. For the said report, including a map indicating the new
outbreaks, go to
<http://www.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=9077>.
- Mod.AS]
